# Testing

## Framework

- Vitest projects: `node` (default), `happy-dom`, and package overlay projects ([ALP-131](https://linear.app/ailuracode/issue/ALP-131/split-vitest-into-node-and-simulated-dom-projects))
- Include pattern: `packages/*/test/**/*.{test,spec}.ts`
- Playwright E2E (root `e2e/playwright.base.ts`, per-package `playwright.config.ts`)
- E2E include pattern: `packages/*/e2e/**/*.spec.ts`
- Inventory: `benchmarks/test-environment-inventory.json` — regenerate with `pnpm run test:classify` (enforced by `repo:check`)
- Performance baseline: `benchmarks/vitest-baseline.json` — refresh with `pnpm run test:benchmark`; compare with `pnpm run test:benchmark:check`
- Tuning evidence: `benchmarks/vitest-tuning-decisions.md` (ALP-134 pool/worker settings in `scripts/vitest-runtime-settings.mjs`)

## Environments

| Target | Use for |
|--------|---------|
| `node` | Controllers, cache, parsing, utilities, SSR imports, repository checks |
| `happy-dom` | Alpine stores, magics, directives, and simulated DOM integration tests (including package overlays) |
| `playwright` | Real browser focus, layout, keyboard, permissions (`packages/<name>/e2e/`) |

Override per file with `// @vitest-environment node` when classification is wrong. Root routing is driven by `scripts/vitest-projects.mjs` and the inventory from `pnpm run test:classify`.

## Harnesses

- Store plugins: use `startAlpine()` from `test/helpers.ts`.
- Magic plugins: use `createMagicHarness()` from `test/mock-alpine.ts`.
- Query cache: use `createQueryClient()` with `vanillaQueryAdapter`.
- `matchMedia`: use `setMatchMedia()` from `test/setup/match-media.ts` (install via `installGlobalMatchMedia()` or `installWindowMatchMedia()` when needed).
- Playwright E2E: use `e2e/fixtures.ts` and package `e2e/fixture/` harnesses.

## Patterns

- Describe block: `describe("@ailuracode/alpine-<name>", () => { … })`.
- Separate `describe("… type inference", …)` blocks with `expectTypeOf` when generics matter.
- Controller logic (directives): test without full Alpine when possible.

## Layer split

Tests MUST be split by layer. Each file has a documented **target environment** in `benchmarks/test-environment-inventory.json`.

| Layer | Filename | Target environment |
|-------|----------|-------------------|
| Controller | `controller.*`, `*Controller.test.ts` | `node` (DOM only when exercising events) |
| Contract | `contract.*`, `encapsulation.*`, `ssr.*` | `node` for SSR; DOM when browser helpers are under test |
| Integration | `plugin.*`, `alpine.integration.*`, `adapter.*`, `magic.*` | `happy-dom` |
| Accessibility | `accessibility.*`, `a11y.*` | `node` or DOM depending on assertions |
| Utility | `parse.*`, `utils.*`, `adapters/**` | `node` |
| Repository | `test/architecture-check.test.ts`, etc. | `node` |
| E2E | `packages/<name>/e2e/*.spec.ts` | `playwright` |

Responsibilities by layer:

- **Controller tests**: initial state, transitions, invariants, events, options, errors, idempotency, cleanup. Import implementation modules directly (`../src/controller.js`). Alpine MUST NOT be initialized unless strictly required.
- **Alpine integration tests**: plugin registration, stores, magics, directives, reactivity, `$dispatch`, expression evaluation, cleanup, multiple instances. Use `startAlpine()` for store/directive plugins or `createMagicHarness()` for magic-only plugins.
- **Accessibility tests**: ARIA props, focus, keyboard navigation, disabled elements, dynamic elements, restore focus, roving tabindex, `aria-activedescendant`.
- **Integration tests**: real external dependencies (Embla initialization/destruction, Floating UI cleanup, browser observers).
- **Contract tests**: import the package entrypoint (`../src/index.js`) or built surface to verify the published API, SSR-safe imports, plugin registration, lifecycle contracts, and multiple independent instances.
- **Packed consumer tests**: import the built `dist/` output the way npm consumers do.
- **E2E tests (Playwright)**: real browser markup and interaction for focus traps, keyboard navigation, portals, scroll locking, layout-sensitive behavior, and browser APIs that happy-dom cannot model faithfully.

Controller-focused files (`controller.spec.ts`, `controller.test.ts`) MUST NOT import `src/index.ts`. Contract, integration, encapsulation, and inference tests MAY import the entrypoint.

E2E specs live in `packages/<name>/e2e/**/*.spec.ts`, are excluded from Vitest, and run with `pnpm --filter @ailuracode/alpine-<name> test:e2e`. See `.cursor/rules/e2e-testing.mdc` and `docs/e2e-testing.md`.

## Thresholds

Every behavior change MUST include tests. Global thresholds MUST NOT be lowered.

## Common mistakes

| Mistake | Fix |
|---------|-----|
| Test store plugin with `createMagicHarness` | Use `startAlpine(plugin)` from `test/helpers.ts` |
| Test magic-only plugin with `startAlpine` + DOM | Use `createMagicHarness(plugin)` from `test/mock-alpine.ts` |
| Import `src/index.ts` from `controller.spec.ts` | Import `../src/controller.js` and related modules directly |
| Contract test imports implementation modules only | Contract/integration tests SHOULD import `../src/index.js` |
| Theme/media tests fail on `matchMedia` | Call `setMatchMedia(query, matches)` from `test/setup.ts` |
| Tests leak `localStorage` / DOM state | Rely on `test/setup/dom-reset.ts` via project setupFiles — don't skip cleanup |
| Import test helpers without `.js` | `import { startAlpine } from "../../../test/helpers.js"` |
| Assert Alpine reactivity without real Alpine | Magic harness uses plain objects — no reactivity there |
| Put E2E specs in Vitest `test/` | Use `packages/<name>/e2e/*.spec.ts` with Playwright |
| Add/rename tests without updating inventory | Run `pnpm run test:classify` and commit `benchmarks/test-environment-inventory.json` |
| Use `page.waitForTimeout()` in E2E | Prefer Playwright auto-waiting and `expect(locator)` |

Run `pnpm test` and `pnpm run lint` before finishing.
